  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink246-kilavi">varaiyātu vantoḻukun talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉāy niṉṟuḻi yavaṉ kēṭkum āṟṟāl veṟi nikaḻāniṉṟamai tōḻi talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu.    </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> The confidante telling the heroine about the Veṟi taking place, in a way that the hero—who kept coming without marrying—could hear, as he stood behind the hedge.
  
          
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink246">
<l>veṟiceṟit taṉaṉē vēlaṉ kaṟiya</l>
<l>kaṉmukai vayappuli kaḻaṅkumeyp paṭūu</l>
<l>meymmai yaṉṉa peṇpāṟ puṇarntu</l>
<l>maṉṟiṟ paiyu ṭīruṅ</l>
<l>kuṉṟa nāṭa ṉuṟīiya nōyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The Vēlaṉ priest has set up the Veṟi</l>
        <l>for the pain inflicted by the man from the hill country,</l>
        <l rend="space">in which the sorrow </l>
        <l rend="space indent2">of the strong tiger from the black mountain cavern</l>
        <l rend="space">is remedied in the village common,</l>
        <l>having united with its female counterpart,</l>
        <l>as though real, made authentic with Molucca beans.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
